## Hard rules

1. **One Task sub-agent** is enough for this work (single FIX-10 hop). Only split into batches if the first Task times out mid-`record`.
2. `subagent_type: generalPurpose`, `run_in_background: false`, `description: FIX-10 sandbox fuzzy`.
3. Stack from current tip (expected: `megiddo/i-validate-idiom-audit` or later). Branch: `megiddo/p3-fix-10-sandbox-fuzzy-rebaseline`.
4. **test profile only** for record. Mirror may ride along in setpoint capture as unchanged bytes.
5. No push/PR unless user asked.
6. Stage seed tooling if still uncommitted, then baseline/setpoint changes. Prefer **two commits** if both exist: (1) seed-test-credentials, (2) FIX-10 baselines.
7. Stop and ask on: seed failure, two consecutive record failures on same page, isolation regression.

## Procedure

1. User-visible: `Starting FIX-10…`
2. Launch Task with preamble + entire FIX-10 worker fenced prompt.
3. Wait for completion; verify gates and report.

